{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.17",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 17,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 17",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 17 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.17.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:1",
      "text": "My spirit is broken, my days are extinct, the grave is ready for me.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.17.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:2",
      "text": "Surely there are mockers about me, and my eye dwells on their provocation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.17.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:3",
      "text": "“Lay down a pledge for me with thyself; who is there that will give surety for me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.17.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:4",
      "text": "Since thou hast closed their minds to understanding, therefore thou wilt not let them triumph.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.17.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:5",
      "text": "He who informs against his friends to get a share of their property, the eyes of his children will fail.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.17.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:6",
      "text": "“He has made me a byword of the peoples, and I am one before whom men spit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.17.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:7",
      "text": "My eye has grown dim from grief, and all my members are like a shadow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.17.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:8",
      "text": "Upright men are appalled at this, and the innocent stirs himself up against the godless.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.17.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:9",
      "text": "Yet the righteous holds to his way, and he that has clean hands grows stronger and stronger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.17.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:10",
      "text": "But you, come on again, all of you, and I shall not find a wise man among you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.17.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:11",
      "text": "My days are past, my plans are broken off, the desires of my heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.17.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:12",
      "text": "They make night into day; ‘The light,’ they say, ‘is near to the darkness.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.17.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:13",
      "text": "If I look for Sheol as my house, if I spread my couch in darkness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.17.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:14",
      "text": "if I say to the pit, ‘You are my father,’ and to the worm, ‘My mother,’ or ‘My sister,’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.17.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:15",
      "text": "where then is my hope? Who will see my hope?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.17.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:16",
      "text": "Will it go down to the bars of Sheol? Shall we descend together into the dust?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
